A MAN has shot and killed his ex-girlfriend and her daughter before turning the gun on himself. The 38-year-old allegedly went to the woman's house in Leana Hof, Bela-Bela, Limpopo, on Saturday, 25 February and fired some shots at the woman (34) and her daughter (11) without saying anything before killing himself. ALSO READ: MUM and her three children hacked to death! The police were notified about the incident and upon arrival with emergency services, the three were all certified dead at the scene. According to police spokesman, Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo in a statement, preliminary investigations revealed that the man stole his friend's firearm. Limpopo Police Commissioner, Lieutenant-General Thembi Hadebe, said:  "We are saddened by this tragic incident because innocent lives continue to be lost at the hands of men who seem to be inclined to committing acts of gender-based violence at any moment the relationship collapses. People experiencing relationship challenges are urged to seek assistance and desist from resorting to extreme violence." REGISTER TO COMMENT Mojapelo added that the police have opened cases of double murder, inquest, theft of firearm and possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition.